**Segments**

- **By Type**: The smart pneumatic valve market can be segmented by type into on/off valve, flow control valve, and others. On/off valves are used to start or stop the flow of fluids by opening or closing the valve mechanism. Flow control valves, on the other hand, are designed to regulate the flow rate of fluids passing through the valve. Other types of smart pneumatic valves may include pressure relief valves, pressure regulating valves, and proportional valves among others.
- **By End-User Industry**: The market for smart pneumatic valves can also be segmented by end-user industry, including oil & gas, water & wastewater treatment, automotive, chemical, food & beverage, and others. Smart pneumatic valves find applications in various industries for controlling the flow of fluids, gases, or air in different processes.
- **By Region**: Geographically, the global smart pneumatic valve market can be segmented into North America, Europe, Asia Pacific, Latin America, and Middle East & Africa. Each region has its own set of market dynamics, key players, and growth opportunities in the smart pneumatic valve market.

